					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I don't know about handling all the obscure cases, but <em>the</em> most important thing is to tell the user that the write failed, so that he knows the file is likely corrupt. A program might further avoid deleting or replacing some known-good file in this case.
<br />
<br />I mentioned this simply because many programmers think that you can simply check the result after an fwrite()/fputc()/etc., missing that last possibly-failing buffer flush/finalize that fclose() does.</div>

