						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">hyarion wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">i would say; just leave it there, or place an assertion on eof if you want to debug it more easily</div>
<br />An fclose() failing isn't a program bug; it's a normal occurrence in some run-time cases. Using assert() to catch this is itself a bug, since assert is for finding bugs in the program, not validating external conditions. So maybe in this case assert is finding a bug, that being the assert itself. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

