						<div class="postbody"><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">FILE* out = fopen&#40; &quot;out&quot;, &quot;wb&quot; &#41;;<br />if &#40; out == NULL &#41;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; fatal_error&#40; &quot;Couldn't open output&quot; &#41;;<br /><br />if &#40; fwrite&#40; data, 1, size, out &#41; &lt; size &#41;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; fatal_error&#40; &quot;Couldn't write data&quot; &#41;;<br /><br />fputc&#40; 0xFF, out &#41;;<br /><br />if &#40; ferror&#40; out &#41; &#41;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; fatal_error&#40; &quot;Couldn't write data&quot; &#41;;<br /><br />// We handled all the usual errors, including disk write errors, correct?<br /><br />fclose&#40; out &#41;;<br /><br />remove&#40; &quot;in&quot; &#41;;<br /><br />// Whoops, disk was fill, and we deleted the input. User deletes us.</div>
<br />
<br />In other words, if you don't check fclose(), you might as well not check any of the others.</div>

