					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">blargg wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">For a GUI-based program, you should use an atomic replace. At least on Apple's platforms, there is a call that atomically swaps two files' contents.</div>
<br />And under any other UNIX environment, rename(2) has the same behavior. But I expect a lot of my users to be on Windows XP, where rename() returns -1 and sets errno to EPERM or EACCES (I forget which) if the destination file exists. MoveFileTransacted(), which performs an atomic replace, wasn't added to Windows until Windows Vista.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

